From 97c24b3e1e057a5e5292037137521d71182101ef Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Cole Walker <cole.walker@windriver.com>
Date: Tue, 10 Feb 2026 09:58:46 -0500
Subject: [PATCH] port: Fix segfault when best master becomes unavailable

When using hybrid E2E mode or unicast client with multiple masters,
ptp4l could segfault if the best master stopped sending messages or
if the port transitioned states while unicast timers were active.
This occurred due to NULL pointer dereferences when accessing the
best foreign master's message queue.

Problem Description:

Two related NULL pointer dereference issues were identified:

1. In port_delay_request() with hybrid_e2e Mode
   When hybrid_e2e is enabled, the code accesses p->best->messages
   to get the destination address for the delay request:

   struct ptp_message *dst = TAILQ_FIRST(&p->best->messages);
   msg->address = dst->address;

   However, if the best master stops sending messages or the port
   loses its best master selection, p->best can be NULL or the
   message queue can be empty, causing a segfault when dereferencing
   TAILQ_FIRST().

2. In unicast_client_timer()
   The timer callback was missing a check for unicast_client_enabled(),
   allowing it to execute even when the unicast client was not properly
   initialized or had been cleaned up. This could occur during port
   state transitions or when the port was being reconfigured.

Root Cause:

The code assumed that p->best and its message queue would always be
valid when these functions were called. However, several scenarios
can invalidate these assumptions:

- Master stops sending ANNOUNCE messages
- ANNOUNCE_RECEIPT_TIMEOUT expires
- Port transitions from SLAVE to LISTENING/FAULTY
- BMC selects local clock as best master (p->best becomes NULL)
- Port reconfiguration or cleanup in progress

In these cases, the port may still have active timers (delay request
timer, unicast client timer) that fire before the port state machine
has fully transitioned, leading to NULL pointer access.

The Fix:

1. Add NULL/Empty Check in port_delay_request()
   Before accessing p->best->messages in hybrid_e2e mode, verify that:
   - p->best is not NULL
   - The message queue is not empty

   if (!p->best || TAILQ_EMPTY(&p->best->messages)) {
       pr_debug("port %hu: no best master for delay request", portnum(p));
       goto out;
   }

   This prevents the segfault and allows the port to gracefully skip
   the delay request when no valid master is available. The delay
   request will be retried on the next timer expiration once a master
   is available again.

2. Add Early Return in unicast_client_timer()
   Check if unicast client is enabled before processing timer events:

   if (!unicast_client_enabled(p)) {
       return 0;
   }

   This prevents the timer from executing when the unicast client is
   not initialized or has been cleaned up, avoiding potential NULL
   pointer dereferences in the unicast master table iteration.

Why These Checks Are Safe:

- Skipping a delay request when no master is available is acceptable;
  the port cannot measure path delay without a master anyway
- The delay request timer will fire again, and if a master is available
  at that time, the request will be sent normally
- Returning early from unicast_client_timer() when disabled is safe;
  the timer should not be active in this state anyway
- These are defensive checks that handle edge cases during state
  transitions

Testing:

Verified the fix by:
- Running with hybrid_e2e mode and stopping/starting master
- Forcing ANNOUNCE_RECEIPT_TIMEOUT by blocking master traffic
- Rapidly switching between multiple masters
- Port state transitions (SLAVE -> FAULTY -> LISTENING)
- No segfaults observed in any scenario
- Port recovers gracefully when master becomes available again

Impact:

This fix prevents crashes in production environments where master
availability cannot be guaranteed. The port now handles master loss
gracefully and continues operating when the master returns.

Signed-off-by: Cole Walker <cole.walker@windriver.com>
---
 port.c           | 4 ++++
 unicast_client.c | 4 ++++
 2 files changed, 8 insertions(+)

diff --git a/port.c b/port.c
index 94c946a..3eb3114 100644
--- a/port.c
+++ b/port.c
@@ -1423,6 +1423,10 @@ int port_delay_request(struct port *p)
 	msg->header.logMessageInterval = 0x7f;
 
 	if (p->hybrid_e2e) {
+		if (!p->best || TAILQ_EMPTY(&p->best->messages)) {
+			pr_debug("port %hu: no best master for delay request", portnum(p));
+			goto out;
+		}
 		struct ptp_message *dst = TAILQ_FIRST(&p->best->messages);
 		msg->address = dst->address;
 		msg->header.flagField[0] |= UNICAST;
diff --git a/unicast_client.c b/unicast_client.c
index e11e5fd..8a015ca 100644
--- a/unicast_client.c
+++ b/unicast_client.c
@@ -551,6 +551,10 @@ int unicast_client_timer(struct port *p)
 	struct unicast_master_address *master;
 	int err = 0;
 
+	if (!unicast_client_enabled(p)) {
+		return 0;
+	}
+
 	pr_debug("port %d: [UC_TIMER] Unicast client timer fired", portnum(p));
 
 	STAILQ_FOREACH(master, &p->unicast_master_table->addrs, list) {
-- 
